# No overrides. pnpm uses its default virtual store at node_modules/.pnpm.
#
# NOTE: earlier revisions set `virtual-store-dir=/tmp/pnpm-dailyriff-vs` as a
# Windows/OneDrive workaround to keep the virtual store off the synced path.
# That broke Linux CI — /tmp is a size-limited tmpfs and pnpm's worker
# crashed silently trying to stage 1191 hardlinks there. Windows developers
# who want the old behavior should set it locally (not in-repo) via
# `pnpm config set virtual-store-dir --location=user ~/pnpm-stores/dailyriff`.
